    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1902-09-06T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1902-09-06T00:00:00-05:00" n="687"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d687">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Iddings</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Hay</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Rome</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1902-09-06">
                            <hi rend="italic">September 6, 1902</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Referring to your unnumbered instruction of
                    August 12 last, and to the Department’s circular<note n="a" xml:id="d687fna"
                        >Printed under Austria, <ref target="#pg_42">page 42</ref>.</note> of August
                    11, I have the honor to report that, as directed, I have to-day shown to the
                    minister for foreign affairs the communication concerning the treatment of Jews
                    in Roumania, and at his request left a copy of the same with him.</p>
                <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lewis Morris Iddings.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
